CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 30, 1954, pg. 14 reads: "Entering Baby Contest - Entries for Carnation Milk's healthy baby contest are pouring into the Courier office. Mrs. Ruth Anderson, 6704 Rowan Avenue, is shown dropping baby Carolyn's entry into the mail.  The contest features six cash prizes totaling $500.  Entries must be postmarked no later than midnight Nov. 17.  watch the Courier for further developments. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Ruth Anderson, wearing tweed skirt and light colored blouse, holding daughter Carolyn with letter, in front of mailbox, possibly on Rowan Avenue, with businesses in background with signs reading "A. Mosesso Contractor...Inselbric" and "Beverages Drive In"
